Data//Economic//Core Business Statistics Series Comparative Statistics for the US and States (1997-2002; 2002-2007; 2007-2012)//Comparative Statistics for the United States and the States (2002 and 1997).xls
column4:
UNIVERSE DESCRIPTION
The universe of this file is all operating establishments with one or more paid employees. This universe includes all establishments classified in the North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) Codes 211111 through 812999.

column2: Data//Economic//Core Business Statistics Series Comparative Statistics for the US and States (1997-2002; 2002-2007; 2007-2012)//Comparative Statistics for the United States and the States (2002 and 1997).xls

Data//Economic//Core Business Statistics Series Comparative Statistics for the US and States (1997-2002; 2002-2007; 2007-2012)//Comparative Statistics for the United States and the States (2002 and 1997).xls
column4:
DATA ITEMS
This file contains data on:

    •  Number of establishments
    •  Sales, receipts, revenue, shipments, or business done
    •  Payroll
    •  Employment
GEOGRAPHIC COVERAGE
The data are shown at the U.S. level and by State.
INDUSTRY DETAIL
The data are shown at the 2- and 3-digit NAICS code levels for all sectors, and by 2- through 8-digit NAICS code levels for selected sectors.
OTHER VARIABLES IDENTIFYING RECORDS
None.
RELEASE SCHEDULE
The data from the Core Business Statistics Comparative Statistics report are to be released in July 2006.
RELATED DATA FILES
Data supersede those released in the Industry, Geographic Area, and Summary Series reports.
CORRESPONDENCE TO PRINTED/PDF REPORTS
These data are exactly the same as are shown in the PDF-format Core Business Statistics Comparative Statistics Report EC02-00-CCOMP. This report is available on the Census Bureau's Internet site at www.census.gov.
DATA LIMITATIONS
There are no special limitations to these data.
FILE SEQUENCE
Data are presented in ascending State by NAICS Code sequence.

Data//Economic//Core Business Statistics Series Comparative Statistics for the US and States (1997-2002; 2002-2007; 2007-2012)//Comparative Statistics for the United States and the States (2007 and 2002).xls
column4:
Universe Description
The universe of this file is all operating establishments with one or more paid employees. (Nonemployer establishments are excluded.) This universe includes all establishments classified in the North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) Codes 211111 through 812999.

column2: Data//Economic//Core Business Statistics Series Comparative Statistics for the US and States (1997-2002; 2002-2007; 2007-2012)//Comparative Statistics for the United States and the States (2007 and 2002).xls

Data//Economic//Core Business Statistics Series Comparative Statistics for the US and States (1997-2002; 2002-2007; 2007-2012)//Comparative Statistics for the United States and the States (2007 and 2002).xls
column4:
Data Items
This file contains data on:

    •  Number of establishments
    •  Sales, receipts, revenue, shipments, or value of business done
    •  Annual payroll
    •  Total employment
Geographic Coverage
The data are shown at the U.S. and State levels.
Industry Detail
The data are shown at the 2- through 6-digit NAICS code levels for all sectors at the National level and at the 2- and 3-digit NAICS code levels for all sectors by state. Data are also shown by state at the 4- through 6-digit NAICS code levels for selected sectors.
Other Variables Identifying Records
The data are shown for all establishments; no breakout is available by Type of Operation (for the Wholesale Trade sector) or by Tax Status (for selected Services sectors.)
Release Schedule
The data in this file are scheduled for release in June 2011.
Related Data Files
The data in this file supersede those released in the Industry, Geographic Area, and Summary Series files.
Data Limitations
Data are shown for selected industries following cutoffs that vary by industry and state. Data are also subject to sampling and nonsampling errors. See Survey Methodology for information on data limitations.
File Sequence
Data are presented in ascending geography (GEO_ID) by NAICS code (NAICS2002) Code sequence.
Estimated File Size
Approx. 4 MB

column2: Data//Economic//Core Business Statistics Series Comparative Statistics for the US and States (1997-2002; 2002-2007; 2007-2012)//Comparative Statistics for the United States and the States (2007 and 2002).xls

Data//Economic//Core Business Statistics Series Comparative Statistics for the US and States (1997-2002; 2002-2007; 2007-2012)//Comparative Statistics for the United States and the States (2007 and 2002).xls
column4:
Source: U.S. Census Bureau, 2007 Economic Census
The data in this file are based on the 2007 and 2002 Economic Censuses. To maintain confidentiality, the Census Bureau suppresses data to protect the identity of any business or individual. The census results in this file contain sampling and non-sampling error. Data users who create their own estimates using data from this file should cite the Census Bureau as the source of the original data only. For the full technical documentation, see Survey Methodology [pdf].
Railroad transportation and U.S. Postal Service are out of scope for the 2007 Economic Census. Large certificated air passenger carriers are included in the 2007 data, not included in the 2002 data, affecting comparability for this industry.
